_json.gridTitle: PlantFiles Pictures: Polyantha Rose 'Mademoiselle Cecile Brunner' (Rosa) by Angel_D
_json.description: 'Cecile Brunner': the 'Sweetheart Rose'(USA), a small, repeat- blooming Polyantha hybridized in 1881 by Pernet- Ducher. The climbing 'Cecile Brunner', actually named "Bloomfield Abundance," can be distinguished by examining the sepals, as one sepal usually extends itself into a small leaf. Cecile Brunner was the daughter of M.Ulrich Brunner, a rose-grower of Lausanne. The full name is actually "Mlle. Cecile Brunner" , never Cecil, as some people persist in calling her.
